  "text": "During the course of these experiments, we also assayed all 13 of our selected longevity strains, spanning long-, short-and normal-lived strains, for their specific activity of 17 different metabolic enzymes involved in the glycolytic, citric acid, and pentose shunt pathways. Only a portion of these data have been presented elsewhere and were consistent with our other work showing that extended longevity in our selected strains is dependent on an early up-regulation of the ADS genes [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
